Package gsonpath

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    GsonArrayStreamer<T>
    Exposes functionality to obtain an array directly from a json file without declaring a container class, or extending a collection directly.
    GsonArrayStreamer.StreamCallback<T>
    A callback used when streaming json array content as opposed to reading the entire array into memory.
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    AbstractGsonArrayStreamer<T>
    A partial implementation of the GsonArrayStreamer which reduces the complexity for code generation since most of the methods can call their overloaded variants.
    GsonArrayStreamer.StreamCallback.StreamHandler
    A handler exposed through the GsonArrayStreamer.StreamCallback which allows stopping a stream midway.
    GsonPath
    The primary class to use when using the GsonPath library.
    GsonUtil
    A set of Gson utilities which expose functionality to read content from a JsonReader safely without throwing IOExceptions.
  • Enum Summary 
    Enum Description
    GsonFieldValidationType
    Specifies what type of validation should be done during Gson parsing.
    GsonPathFieldNamingPolicy
    Provides the exact same functionality as the Gson FieldNamingPolicy enum, however this class was created to provide an easy way to inherit a default value if required by using the GsonPathFieldNamingPolicy.IDENTITY_OR_INHERIT_DEFAULT_IF_AVAILABLE variation of the GsonPathFieldNamingPolicy.IDENTITY value.
    InheritableBoolean
    Created due to a requirement to specify a boolean value on an annotation which may potentially be replaced with a default value if the enum has specified that it inherits.
  • Exception Summary 
    Exception Description
    JsonFieldMissingException  
  • Annotation Types Summary 
    Annotation Type Description
    AutoGsonAdapter
    A class annotated with this annotation will automatically generate a Gson TypeAdapter at compile time.
    AutoGsonArrayStreamer
    A class annotated with this annotation will automatically generate a Gson GsonArrayStreamer at compile time.
    ExcludeField
    Specifies that the annotated field will not be added to the auto generated TypeAdapter when using the AutoGsonAdapter annotation.
    FlattenDelimiter
    Defines a delimiter character used by the Gson Path library when dealing with nested fields.
    FlattenJson
    Specifies that the JSON object found for this field should be flattened into a String.
    GsonPathDefaultConfiguration
    Specifies a set of default values for the AutoGsonAdapter class.
    PathSubstitution
    Provides a text substitution mechanism to the com.google.gson.annotations.SerializedName annotation when used in conjunction with the AutoGsonAdapter.
